# Test Case 

## Test Details

* Test Case ID:
  * 02
* Test Case Name:
  * Test number 02
* Component: 
  *  Game Engine Requirements  
* Test Case Designer:
  * Jeremy and Victoria and Matthew
* Creation Date:
  * 10/12/2018
* Modified By:
  * Victoria and Jeremy and Matthew
* Modified Date:
  * 10/12/2018
* Requirements Covered:
  * 1. Must be the first thing that starts when the game is turned on.
  * 2. Will be the only thing that can write to the main game buffer.
  * 3. Must initialize all of the other drivers.
  * 4. Must handle all user input.
  * 5. Will initialize the connection to the database if build mode is picked.
  * 6. Write the bugger to the screen.
* Test Description/Purpose:
  * To be able to test the system to see if its compatable. 
  * This tes is also supposed to make sure that it runs on multiple servers, on different systems.
  
* Pre-Test Conditions:
  * Booting up game to initialize if the game runs or not 
## Test Steps: 
| # | Description | Expected Result | Check (√) |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Make sure that the game runs, and actually starts. | √ |			
| 2 | All drivers will have to go through will have to go through this engine in order to access the components within the game  | √ |			
| 3 | Sets up all drivers | √ |			
| 4 | Must react properly wjere the game user input is being given | √ |			
| 5	| This starts when the player decides to play in online mode. | √ |
| 6 | Appropriate images are shown.   | √ |
## Overall Test Status:
As of this test, everything loaded as projected. the images loaded properly, and all the other screens as well. 

